Utility Container
-----------------
1. Ceph utility Container

Installation
------------
complete the installation of openstack-helm with ceph using the following documentation.

https://docs.openstack.org/openstack-helm/latest/install/index.html

once the installation is completed clone porthole repo to the same folder where in openstack-helm-infra is cloned.

Run install_utility.sh

Usage
-----

Get in to the utility pod using kubectl exec. To perform any operation on the ceph cluster use the below example.

example:
   nccli ceph osd tree
   nccli rbd ls
   nccli rados lspools


